  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d0ec49142d5c7c24fb05ee739840cab0, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elimelech Takes His Family to Live in Moab'
      title: Elimelech Takes His Family to Live in Moab
      number: 1
      content: "And it happened in the days when the judges ruled, there was a famine
        in the land, and a man from Bethlehem of Judah went to reside in the countryside
        of Moab\u2014he and his wife and his two sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the name of the man was Elimelech, and the name of his wife was
        Naomi, and the names of his two sons were Mahlon and Kilion. They were Ephraimites
        from Bethlehem in Judah. And they went to the countryside of Moab and remained
        there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But Elimelech the husband of Naomi died and she was left behind with
        her two sons.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they took for themselves Moabite wives. The name of the one was
        Orpah and the name of the other was Ruth. And they lived there about ten
        years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Naomi Returns with Ruth'
      title: Naomi Returns with Ruth
      number: 5
      content: 'But both Mahlon and Kilion died, and the woman was left without her
        two sons and without her husband. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And she got up, she and her daughters-in-law, and returned from the
        countryside of Moab, because she had heard in the countryside of Moab that
        Yahweh had come to the aid of his people to give food to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So she set out from the place where she was and her two daughters-in-law
        with her, and they went on the way to return to the land of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But Naomi said to her two daughters-in-law, \u201CGo, each of you
        return to her mother\u2019s house. May Yahweh show kindness to you just as
        you did with the dead and with me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "May Yahweh grant that you find a resting place, each in the house
        of her husband.\u201D And she kissed them, and they lifted up their voices
        and cried. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And they said to her, \u201CNo, we want to return with you to your
        people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Naomi said, \u201CReturn, my daughters. Why do you still want
        to go with me? Are there sons in my womb that may be husbands for you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Turn back, my daughters! Go, for I am too old to have a husband.
        If I should think there is hope for me, even if I should have a husband this
        night, and even if I should bear sons, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "would you therefore wait until they were grown? Would you therefore
        refrain from marrying? No, my daughters, for it is far more bitter to me
        than to you. For the hand of Yahweh has gone out against me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And they lifted up their voices and cried again. And Orpah kissed
        her mother-in-law goodbye, but Ruth clung to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And she said, \u201CLook, your sister-in-law has returned to her
        people and to her gods. Return after your sister-in-law too.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But Ruth said, \u201CDo not urge me to leave you or to return from
        following you! For where you go, I will go, and where you lodge, I will lodge.
        Your people will be my people and your God will be my God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Where you die I will die, and there I will be buried. So may Yahweh
        do to me, and even more, unless death separates you and me!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When Naomi saw that she was determined to go with her, she said no
        more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So the two of them went until they came to Bethlehem. And when they
        came to Bethlehem, all of the town was stirred because of them. And they
        said, \u201CIs this Naomi?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And she said to them, \u201CYou should not call me Naomi; call me
        Mara, for Shaddai has caused me to be very bitter.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I went away full, but Yahweh brought me back empty-handed! Why call
        me Naomi when Yahweh has testified against me and Shaddai has brought calamity
        upon me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So Naomi returned, and Ruth the Moabite her daughter-in-law with
        her, returning from the countryside of Moab. And they came to Bethlehem at
        the beginning of the harvest of barley. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ruth Meets Boaz'
      title: Ruth Meets Boaz
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Naomi had a relative of her husband, a prominent rich man from
        the clan of Elimelech, whose name was Boaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Ruth the Moabite said to Naomi, \u201CPlease let me go to the
        field and glean among the ears of grain after someone in whose eyes I may
        find favor.\u201D And she said to her, \u201CGo, my daughter.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So she went and came and gleaned in the field behind the reapers.
        And she happened by chance upon the tract of field belonging to Boaz, who
        was from the clan of Elimelech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And look, Boaz came from Bethlehem and said to the reapers, \u201CMay
        Yahweh be with you.\u201D And they said to him, \u201CMay Yahweh bless you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Boaz said to his servant in charge of the reapers, \u201CTo whom
        does this young woman belong?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the servant in charge of the reapers said, \u201CShe is a Moabite
        girl returning with Naomi from the countryside of Moab. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And she said, \u2018Please let me glean and let me gather among the
        sheaves behind the reapers.\u2019 So she came and remained from the morning
        up to now. She is sitting for a little while in the house.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Boaz said to Ruth, \u201CListen carefully, my daughter, go no
        longer to glean in another field. Moreover, do not leave from this one, but
        stay close with my young women. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Keep your eyes on the field that they reap and go after them. Have
        I not ordered the servants not to bother you? And if you get thirsty, you
        shall go to the containers and drink from where the servants have drawn.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And she fell on her face and bowed down to the ground and said to
        him, \u201CWhy have I found favor in your eyes by recognizing me\u2014for
        I am a foreigner?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Boaz answered and said to her, \u201CAll that you have done for
        your mother-in-law after the death of your husband was fully told to me.
        How you left your father and mother and the land of your birth, and you went
        to a people that you did not know before.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "May Yahweh reward your work and may a full reward be given to you
        from Yahweh, the God of Israel, under whose wings you came to take refuge.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And she said, \u201CMay I find favor in your eyes, my lord, for you
        have comforted me and have spoken kindly to your servant, and I am not one
        of your servants.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Boaz said to her at mealtime, \u201CCome here and eat from the
        bread and dip your morsel in the wine vinegar.\u201D So she sat beside the
        gleaners, and he offered to her roasted grain. And she ate and was satisfied,
        and she had some left over. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And she got up to glean, and Boaz instructed his servants saying,
        \u201CLet her also glean between the sheaves and do not reproach her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And also pull out for her from your bundles and leave it so that
        she may glean\u2014and do not rebuke her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So she gleaned in the field until the evening and she beat out what
        she had gleaned, and it was about an ephah of barley. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And she picked it up and went to the town. Her mother-in-law saw
        how much she had gleaned. And she took it out and gave to her what she had
        left over after being satisfied.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And her mother-in-law said to her, \u201CWhere did you glean today
        and where did you work? May he who took notice of you be blessed.\u201D And
        she told her mother-in-law with whom she had worked and said, \u201CThe name
        of the man who I worked with today is Boaz.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Naomi said to her daughter-in-law, \u201CMay he be blessed by
        Yahweh, whose loyal love has not forsaken the living or the dead.\u201D And
        Naomi said to her, \u201CThe man is a close relative for us, he is one of
        our redeemers.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Ruth the Moabite said, \u201CAlso, he said to me, \u2018You shall
        stay close with the servants which are mine until they have finished all
        of the harvest which is mine.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And Naomi said to Ruth her daughter-in-law, \u201CIt is good, my
        daughter, that you go out with his maidservants so that you will not be bothered
        in another field.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So she stayed close with the maidservants of Boaz to glean until
        the end of the barley harvest and wheat harvest. And she lived with her mother-in-law. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ruth Meets Boaz at the Threshing Floor'
      title: Ruth Meets Boaz at the Threshing Floor
      number: 1
      content: "Now Naomi her mother-in-law said to her, \u201CMy daughter, should
        I not seek for you security that things may be good for you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So then, is not Boaz our kinsman whose maidservants you were with?
        Look, he is winnowing the barley at the threshing floor tonight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Wash, anoint yourself, put your clothing on, and go down to the threshing
        floor. Do not make yourself known to the man until he finishes eating and
        drinking. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And when he lies, take notice of the place where he lies. And you
        shall go and uncover his feet and lie down, and he shall tell you what to
        do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And she said to her, \u201CI will do all that you say.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And she went down to the threshing floor and did all that her mother-in-law
        had instructed her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And Boaz ate and drank until his heart was merry and then he came
        to lie at the end of the grain heap. And she came in quietly and uncovered
        his feet and lay down. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And it happened in the middle of the night the man was startled and
        he reached out and behold, a woman was lying at his feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And he said, \u201CWho are you?\u201D And she said, \u201CI am Ruth,
        your servant. Spread your garment over your servant because you are a redeemer.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And he said, \u201CYou are blessed by Yahweh my daughter. You did
        better in this last kindness than the first by not going after young men,
        whether poor or rich. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And so then my daughter, do not be afraid. All that you ask I will
        do for you, for the entire assembly of my people knows that you are a worthy
        woman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now truly I am a redeemer, but there is also a redeemer of a closer
        relationship than me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Stay tonight, and in the morning, if he wants to redeem you, good;
        but if he is not willing to redeem, then as Yahweh lives, I will redeem you.
        Lie down until the morning.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So she lay at his feet until morning and got up before anyone could
        recognize each other. And he said, \u201CIt must not be known that you came
        to the threshing floor.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And he said, \u201CBring the cloak that is on you and hold it out.\u201D
        And she held it out and he measured six measures of barley and put it on
        her cloak. Then she went into the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And she came to her mother-in-law, and she said, \u201CHow did it
        go for you, my daughter?\u201D And she told her all that the man did for
        her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And she said, \u201CThese six measures of barley he gave to me, for
        he said, \u2018You shall not go empty-handed to your mother-in-law.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And she said, \u201CWait, my daughter, until you know how the matter
        turns out, for the man will not rest but will settle the matter today.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Boaz Redeems Ruth'
      title: Boaz Redeems Ruth
      number: 1
      content: "And Boaz had gone up to the city gate and sat there. And look, the
        redeemer of whom Boaz had spoken was passing by. And he said, \u201CCome
        over here to sit, friend.\u201D And he came over and sat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he took ten men from the elders of the city and said, \u201CSit
        here.\u201D And they sat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And he said to the redeemer, \u201CNaomi, who returned from the countryside
        of Moab, is selling the tract of land which was for our brother Elimelech. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And I thought I would tell you and say, \u2018Buy it in the presence
        of those sitting and before the elders of my people,\u2019 if you want to
        redeem it, redeem it. But if you do not want to redeem, tell me so that I
        may know, for there is no one except you to redeem it, and I am after you.\u201D
        And he said, \u201CI want to redeem it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Boaz said, \u201COn the day of your acquiring the field from
        the hand of Naomi, you also acquire Ruth the Moabite, the wife of the dead
        man, in order to raise up for the name of the dead his inheritance.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the redeemer said, \u201CI am not able to redeem for myself,
        lest I ruin my inheritance. You redeem for yourself my kinsman-redemption,
        for I am not able to redeem it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '(Now this was the custom in former times in Israel concerning the
        kinsman-redemption and transfer of property: to confirm the matter, a man
        removed his sandal and gave it to his fellow countryman. This was the manner
        of attesting in Israel.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So the redeemer said to Boaz, \u201CAcquire it for yourself,\u201D
        and he removed his sandal. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Boaz said to the elders and all of the people, \u201CYou are
        witnesses today that I have acquired all that was for Elimelech and that
        was for Kilion and Mahlon from the hand of Naomi. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And also Ruth the Moabite, the wife of Mahlon, I have acquired as
        a wife, to raise up the name of the dead over his inheritance, so that the
        name of the dead may not be cut off from his relatives and from the gate
        of his birth place. You are witnesses today.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And all of the people who were at the gate and the elders said, \u201CWe
        are witnesses. May Yahweh make the woman coming into your house as Rachel
        and as Leah, who together built the house of Israel. May you have strength
        in Ephrathah and bestow a name in Bethlehem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Lineage of King David'
      title: The Lineage of King David
      number: 12
      content: "And may your house be like the house of Perez, whom Tamar bore to
        Judah from the offspring that Yahweh will give to you from this young woman.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Boaz took Ruth and she became his wife. And he went in to her,
        and Yahweh enabled her to conceive, and she bore a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And the women said to Naomi, \u201CBlessed be Yahweh who today did
        not leave you without a redeemer! And may his name be renowned in Israel! "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He shall be for you a restorer of life and a sustainer in your old
        age, for your daughter-in-law who loves you, who is better for you than seven
        sons, has borne him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Naomi took the child and she put him on her bosom and became
        his nurse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the women of the neighborhood gave him a name, saying, \u201CA
        son has been born to Naomi.\u201D And they called his name Obed. He was the
        father of Jesse, the father of David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now these are the descendants of Perez: Perez fathered Hezron, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and Hezron fathered Ram, and Ram fathered Amminadab, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and Amminadab fathered Nahshon, and Nahshon fathered Salmon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and Salmon fathered Boaz, and Boaz fathered Obed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and Obed fathered Jesse, and Jesse fathered David. '
      comments: []
